							<tr bgcolor="#ffffff">
							
								<td width="10">&nbsp;</td>	
								<td colspan="2"><br>
								<!--<h4>EQDiva News</h4>-->
	<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="98%">
<tr bgcolor="#333366"><td valign="bottom" colspan="2" class="clsBoldWhite">&nbsp;&nbsp;Big Patch is out! We run like the wind again!</b></td></tr>
<tr bgcolor="#9999cc"><td valign="bottom" class="clsSmall">&nbsp;<i>Kocho Divah</i></td><td valign="bottom" align="right" class="clsSmall">&nbsp;&nbsp;Wednesday, January 17, 2001&nbsp;&nbsp;7:21pm CST</b></td></tr>
<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#eeeeee"><br><blockquote>The wondrous patch is out! What the bottom line to this patch is that all Everquestors will level faster! I was one of the first on the server to test out our beloved Selo's song to confirm it works correctly, and yes, we fly like the wind again.</blockquote></td></tr>
<tr><td colspan="2" align="right"><img src="/images/buttons/imgDrum.gif"><br><br></td></tr>
<tr bgcolor="#333366"><td valign="bottom" colspan="2" class="clsBoldWhite">&nbsp;&nbsp;Changes - Link to Producer's letter</b></td></tr>
<tr bgcolor="#9999cc"><td valign="bottom" class="clsSmall">&nbsp;<i>Kocho Divah</i></td><td valign="bottom" align="right" class="clsSmall">&nbsp;&nbsp;Wednesday, January 17, 2001&nbsp;&nbsp;7:07pm CST</b></td></tr>
<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#eeeeee"><br><blockquote>If you haven't heard already, Verant has some huge changes coming our way. Read all about it in the <a href="/news/letters/letter011401.asp">Producer's letter</a> from the Everquest Team.</blockquote></td></tr>
<tr><td colspan="2" align="right"><img src="/images/buttons/imgDrum.gif"><br><br></td></tr>
<tr bgcolor="#333366"><td valign="bottom" colspan="2" class="clsBoldWhite">&nbsp;&nbsp;Selos is Broken! Gasp!</b></td></tr>
<tr bgcolor="#9999cc"><td valign="bottom" class="clsSmall">&nbsp;<i>Kocho Divah</i></td><td valign="bottom" align="right" class="clsSmall">&nbsp;&nbsp;Thursday, January 11, 2001&nbsp;&nbsp;7:00pm CST</b></td></tr>
<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#eeeeee"><br><blockquote>Of latest news is the recent patch Verant put out which broke our beloved Selos song. What happened is that Selos Accelerando, a song bards get at level 5, no longer gives increased running speed with a drum equipped. This is the song that defines a bard, it is definitely my favorite song and is always at the top of my song list.</P><P>I found this bug the hard way when I was running around and something didn't quite feel right. I checked if I had any slow SoW on, or maybe I accidentally had it set to walk... Hmmm... Or my drums equipped? Are they my magical MM drums? Everything was right, but I tossed it off and proceeded into battle. Towards the end of the night, a vicious mountain giant train attacked our camp. I was full health, and my group called out &quot;Zone!&quot; No worry, your trusty bard is here! </P><P>I swooped up all members I could and started high-tailing it for the zone. Now, usually I outdistance myself quite quickly, so that I can safely turn around and usually see the mobs give up on me. Not so, they proceeded to beat me down pretty good, and I escape just barely with a bubble of health. They followed me all the way to the Lake of Ill Omen zone, where a few of my other group members beat me there since they had SoWs. Normally I like to loop back and catch any stragglers in my group to save them. Unfortunately, because of this nerf, my Paladin boyfriend was left behind, and he died. So this isn't something that only affects bards, but their whole group who depend on the bard. Please get a patch for this out ASAP! <BR></blockquote></td></tr>
<tr><td colspan="2" align="right"><img src="/images/buttons/imgDrum.gif"><br><br></td></tr>
